<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.404/126a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>)<note n="11" xml:id="d278fn11">This instruction was sent at the request of
                                    President Roosevelt and the reply, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>,
                                    was transmitted to him.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-22T18:00:00-04:00">July 22, 1935—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>50. Press for last few days has been reporting new measures by German
                                Government applying to religious groups. Would appreciate
                                telegraphic report with comment on subject.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>